libcmime
------------------------------------------
libcmime is a lightweight mime library, written in C. It attempts to be a
general library for parsing and creating mime email messages and is designed
to provide an easy to use and easy to integrate interface for developers.
libcmime is a pretty fresh project so the library is still in beta state and
there will be early and frequent releases.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libcmime-devel-0.2.1-1bl1
  libcmime0.2-0.2.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.28-3
  bison-3.0.4-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  flex-2.6.4-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ruby-2.3.3-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.libcmime.org/

Canonical download:
  http://www.libcmime.org/files/libcmime-0.2.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libcmime-0.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libcmime-0.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcmime-0.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcmime-0.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcmime0.2-0.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcmime-devel-0.2.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libcmime)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libcmime.README
  /usr/share/doc/libcmime/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libcmime/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libcmime/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libcmime/README

(libcmime0.2)
  /usr/bin/cygcmime-0.2.dll

(libcmime-devel)
  /usr/include/cmime.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_address.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_base64.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_config.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_header.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_list.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_message.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_part.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_qp.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_string.h
  /usr/include/cmime/cmime_util.h
  /usr/lib/libcmime.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libcmime.pc

